record_data.record_plain_text: [N] CANCELLATION NOTICE [C] ADOPTION SUPPLEMENT OHIO OIL GATHERING CORPORATION II LOCAL TARIFF GATHERING CHARGES APPLYING ON INTERSTATE TRANSPORTATION OF CRUDE PETROLEUM FROM POINTS IN OHIO AND WEST VIRGINIA TO POINTS IN OHIO [C] Effective September 1, 2012, this tariff will become the tariff of Ohio Oil Gathering II, LLC per its adoption notice F.E.R.C. No. 1.0.0. [N] Effective October 28, 2012, this tariff is hereby canceled. For further rates and routing and rules and regulations, see Ohio Oil Gathering II, LLC's F.E.R.C. No. 2.0.0. Filed in compliance with 18 C.F.R. 341.6 (Adoption) Explanation of Reference Marks [C] Cancel. [N] New. ISSUED: September 27, 2012. EFFECTIVE: October 28, 2012. The provisions published herein will, if effective, not result in an effect on the quality of human environment. Issued by: Paul Weissgarber Ohio Oil Gathering Corporation II 2501 Cedar Springs, Suite 100 Dallas, TX 75201 Compiled by: Paul Weissgarber Ohio Oil Gathering Corporation II 2501 Cedar Springs, Suite 100 Dallas, TX 75201 (214) 721-9384 Facsimile (214) 721-9384 [C] All language reflected below is cancelled. Ohio Oil Gathering Corporation II (hereinafter "Corporation") will not gather crude petroleum for storage. It will gather crude petroleum for transportation and for storage incidental thereto, only when the consignor or consignee has provided the necessary facilities for taking delivery of said crude petroleum as it arrives at destination, at rates and subject to regulation as named below: GATHERING AND TRANSPORTATION Rule 1. Rates: - For gathering crude petroleum from lease tanks and transporting of same from points in Ohio and West Virginia to established delivery points for interstate transportation beyond: POINTS OF ORIGIN DESTINATION CHARGES PER BARREL (42 U.S. GALLONS) FOR SHIPMENTS OF LESS THAN 60 BARRELS AT ANY SINGLE STOP VOLUME INCENTIVE RATE CHARGES PER BARREL (42 U.S. GALLONS) FOR SHIPMENTS OF 60 BARRELS OR MORE AT ANY SINGLE STOP RATE CHARGES PER BARREL (42 U.S. GALLONS) FOR SHIPMENTS OF ANY VOLUME Ohio Zone Athens, Belmont, Coshocton, Delaware, Fairfield, Franklin, Gallia, Guernsey, Hocking, Holmes, Knox, Lawrence, Licking, Logan, Meigs, Monroe, Morgan, Morrow, Muskingum, Noble, Perry, Pickaway, Vinton, Washington Counties, Ohio Bells Run, Washington County, Ohio [U] $4.14 [U] $2.89 N/A West Virginia Zone 1 Marshall, Wetzel, Tyler, Pleasants, Wood, Wirt, Ritchie, and Doddridge Counties, West Virginia [U] $4.20 [U] $2.95 N/A West Virginia Zone 2 Harrison, Lewis, Gilmer, Calhoun, Roane, Jackson, and Mason Counties, West Virginia [U] $5.00 [U] $3.75 N/A West Virginia Zone 3 Boone, Cabell, Putnam, Kanawha, Clay (including Rouzer Station, West Virginia), Braxton, Upshur, Barbour, Lincoln, Randolph, Wayne, Marion, Monongalia and Taylor Counties, West Virginia [U] $5.50 [U] $4.25 N/A West Virginia Zone 4 Richardson, West Virginia and Tariff, West Virginia receipt points N/A N/A [U] $3.75 West Virginia Zone 5 Stockly, West Virginia receipt point [C] Bells Run, Washington County, Ohio N/A N/A [U] $4.25 Rule 2. Mixing with Other Oils: - Crude Petroleum of any specified kind will be accepted for transportation and for storage incidental thereto, only on condition that it shall be subject to such changes in gravity or quality as may result from the mixture of such crude petroleum with other crude petroleum in pipe lines and/or tanks of this Corporation, and that delivery shall be made to consignee out of common stock of such crude petroleum in this Corporation's lines and/or tanks at delivery point. Rule 3. Payment of Charges: - Payment of transportation charges may be demanded before delivery. Rule 4. Deduction: - The Corporation will deduct one percent (1%) from all oil produced and received into the Corporation's custody, to cover evaporation and waste. A further deduction of one twentieth of one percent (1/20%) for each degree Fahrenheit of difference between the temperature of the oil as gathered and the temperature in the vicinity of the gathering site on the date of gathering will be made. Charges will be assessed on the quality of oil actually credited to the owner upon the books of this Corporation. Rule 5. Refusal: - The Corporation reserves the right to refuse to gather if the oil tendered is not of a merchantable quality or if, in the Corporation's sole judgment, gathering would expose employees of the Corporation or their equipment to an undue risk of harm or property damage. Rule 6. Liability of this Company: - While in the possession of the property herein described, this Company shall not be liable for any loss or damage or delay caused by the act of God, public enemy, quarantine, authority of law, strikes, riots, fire, floods, or act or default of consignor or consignee, or from any other cause not due to the negligence of this Company whether similar or dissimilar to the causes herein enumerated. In such cases, the consignor shall stand the loss in the same proportion as the amount accepted for transportation and actually in this Company's custody bears to the whole of the property of all consignors in this Company's custody at the time of such loss and shall be entitled to receive only such portion of its shipment as is left after deducting its due proportion of the loss, as above. Statement of quantities ascertained and computed from the records in the usual manner by this Company shall be accepted as prima facie correct in the distribution of such losses under this rule. This Company will not be liable for discoloration, commingling, contamination, or deterioration of property transported unless same is caused by the negligence of this Company. In case of a loss by fire, if there be held by this Company any insurance against such loss, the benefit of such insurance shall extend to the consignor or party suffering the loss, insofar as this shall not result in the cancellation or termination of the policies or contract of insurance. Rule 7. Claims, Suits, Time for Filing: - As a condition precedent to recovery, claims must be filed in writing with this Company within six months of gathering if pertaining to gathering or six months after delivery of the property or in case of failure to make delivery, then within six months after a reasonable time for delivery has elapsed, and suit shall be instituted against this Company only within two years and one day from the day that notice in writing is given by this Company to the claimant that this Company has disallowed the claim or any part or parts thereof specified in the notice. Where claims for loss or damage are not filed or suits are not instituted thereon in accordance with the foregoing provisions, such claims will not be paid and this Company will not be liable. Rule 8. Pro-ration: - In the event the Company is unable to collect or deliver crude oil due to capacity constraints or a force majeure, all shippers affected by the constraints or the force majeure will be reduced pro rata based upon their average monthly gathered volumes.
